<item>
            <title>[HBASE-4194] RegionSplitter: Split on under-loaded region servers first</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-4194</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When running RegionSplitter, our app devs noticed that they were getting a lot of NSREs.  This is caused by 2 factors: &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1. the split itself will cause an NSRE &lt;br/&gt;
2. any load balancing will cause one.  &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The former cannot be helped.  We can more tightly control load balancing though.  Instead of doing a name-sorted round-robin split across RS in the tier, we could sort the RS&apos;s by region count.  That way, we only split an RS with 10 regions after there are no more RS with 9 regions.  This will prevent the load balancing slop from kicking in and will fix the problem where restarting RegionSplitter always starts splitting at RS #1.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
